That means the remaining problem is very likely not control-plane RPC anymore. It is more likely the data/transport side that UHD tries to bring up after MPM succeeds.

The strongest concrete mismatch still visible is your SFP path:

* sfp0 negotiates at 1 Gb/s
* the E320 guide says for the 1G SFP+ path, both ends should use MTU 1500
* your E320 still shows MTU 9000 on sfp0

That combination can let small control traffic work while higher-level UHD device creation still fails.

What to do next

On the host, first make sure the host-side SDR NIC is 1500:

sudo ip link set dev enx6c6e072c655a down
sudo ip link set dev enx6c6e072c655a mtu 1500
sudo ip link set dev enx6c6e072c655a up
ip addr show enx6c6e072c655a

On the E320, stop the hardware daemon, bring sfp0 down, change the MTU, then bring it back:

systemctl stop usrp-hwd.service
ip link set dev sfp0 down
ip link set dev sfp0 mtu 1500
ip link set dev sfp0 up
ip addr show sfp0
systemctl start usrp-hwd.service

If ip link set dev sfp0 down or mtu 1500 still says Resource busy, reboot the E320 and do the same sequence immediately after it comes back.

